    "summary_tldr": "Across mostly retrospective cohorts, esophageal or double stenting generally yielded longer mean survival than airway stenting alone; initial closure rates were high but recurrence was common, with notable but infrequent serious complications (respiratory failure, hemoptysis, bleeding).",
    "clinical_relevance": "Provides practical, comparative evidence summaries to guide palliative endoscopic management of malignant aerodigestive fistulas, including when to prioritize airway vs esophageal stenting and considerations for double stenting."
